    "actor_description": "It sits in me like a cold stone I keep turning over. My jaw stays tight, my thoughts loop on the same sharp ledger of wrongs, and everything feels slightly rigged against me. I’m not exploding—I’m collecting. The irritation isn’t loud; it’s persistent, and it makes every next step feel heavier than it should.",
